rComments: Prof Maurutto gives clear lectures and uploads the slides. The readings are not too heavy. She is really chill and will spend time to explain or discuss with you. Her TA though - tells you to keep it simple in the research piece but gives you bad mark for not explaining in depth

Good class overall. Lectures are clear and concise, although sometimes boring. Tests are all from lectures (be sure to focus on key concepts). Lots of assignments, but they were marked fairly. Assignments will probably bring your mark down so must optimize on the tests. Textbook and readings not necessary, just listen in class.

She is a great prof overall lectures are interesting and straight forward. However, the TA's during this particular session were extremely difficult in terms of marking. It seemed as if the TA were not being critical or providing constructive criticism of the students work, rather attacking the student on a personal level.

Very knoledgable, clear and informative! I look forward to going to class because I actually learn something. She also uses examples and shows videos to make things interesting. Exams are very fair. Take this class!

She is by far my favourite prof. There's no tricks and she doesn't deviate from the course material. Her lectures are focused and you can be sure they will be on tests/exams. The textbook helps but I only studied the lecture material and got over 80 on both the midterm and the exam! Just be sure to take really good notes during her lectures
Amazing professor and is super nice!

Took PSY209H last fall with her. not sure what other students are writing about absolutely having to go to school. Her lectures were on friday morning and so I hardly attended her classes and still managed to get an A. S/A ques do come out of her lectures, but she uploads her lecture notes. Also, textbook is the easiest I have ever read.

easy to listen to, and makes her lectures interesting. The material is boring but her voice helps keep you awake. Lectures are absolutely mandatory, all long answer questions for the test/exam come from there. In that way, she's predictable. Answers all questions, literally ALL!
excellent! very passionate about what she teaches, can engage a class no problem, lots of real life examples, very through, helpful, i want to be just like her:)

She is a darling lady who is an absolute pleasure to speak with outside of class. Attendance is mandatory--you must go to every class if you want to do well. Tests come more from the lectures than the textbook. The essay is the hardest part of this course. You really need to brush up on your writing skills for both the essay and the tests.
REALLY REALLY REALLY EASY PROF:) all you really need to do is read the textbook which is honestly like a high school textbook. That's all you need to do really well in the class!
Very engaging professor, will sometimes take up a bit too much time by going through lecture slides word for word, but kept things interesting through usage of real life examples and videos.

she was an awesome prof! I reallly enjoyed the material in this class, it was super interesting! as for her teaching style, she very enthusiastic about the material. Her exams are mostly from the lecture slides, especially the ones she has the most written about!!Overall very good prof, easy course!

I really enjoyed her as a prof. Shes straightforward, interesting and  engages you. The tests are straightforward and are based solely on lecture material. If you pay attention and go to class, you'll do well. I wish she was teaching more classes.

Awesome prof. Like everyone said, tests based solely on lectures. Who doesn't love that? Barely read the course reader and still did awesome. Now that's a great course. No stress, just a great learning experience with extremely interesting material. I WISH she was teaching everything Hannah-moffat is teaching. AWESOME PROF. miss her.
I thought she was okay. Basically just went over the slies in lecture, didnt really provide any extra information which was kind of annoying.. tests are straightforward.

Prof Maurutto is approachable, friendly- course is relatively easy but she's a little spacey.  She tries to be helpful, but is not timely at all with e-mail responses. For papers she says she allows any citation format but is clearly unfamiliar with MLA and so are her TAs which is frustrating. Word of advice: use a citation with a year.
took for both 310 and 316 and would take her again if i could for 323, she awesome, great material, test based purely on slides, gives a lot of help for the test...take her if u can!!!

Paula's a great prof. Very friendly & approachable and the courses are pretty easy: You don't have to do the readings for either; tests are strictly lecture-based. Her TA's though are *strict* (on her order I suppose). You have to mention *everything* from the lectures you are writing about to do well. Got over 80 in both without touching the texts

Prof Maurutto is like a coffee crisp.  Not the best candy bar but somewhat 'better than the rest'.  She is passionate & encourages feedback from students.  The course is pretty easy - memorize the slides & you'll do well.  I would recommend this course.  The down fall is it is offered on Fridays so dont drink too much on Thursday night...
